# Cinematch handoff (every chat)

1. **At the start of substantive work** in this repo, open **`PASSDOWN-NEXT-CHAT.md`** for workflow, backlog, ops, and **last session** (slim file). Use **`HANDOFF.md`** for architecture and stable product depth (PWA, watchlist, caps, etc.). **`PASSDOWN-ARCHIVE.md`** holds legacy narrative if needed.
2. **Recurring reminder:** neighbor **`pg_cron`** only covers **`jobs × limit`** users per wave. When **`user_neighbors`**, **compute-neighbors**, **cron**, **pg_net**, or **user / MAU growth** comes up, remind to check **`COMPUTE-NEIGHBORS-CRON.md`** and expand staggered **`offset`** / **`cron.schedule`** rows so all eligible non-seed users are covered.
3. When the user asks to **“update passdown”**, **“passdown”**, **“write a handoff (for the next chat)”**, **“handoff file for next chat”**, or after shipping meaningful neighbor/match/cron changes: **edit `PASSDOWN-NEXT-CHAT.md`** (date, recent work, open follow-ups) using the same checklist. **In the same reply, always give the user a short, ready-to-paste block — *What to tell the next chat* —** distilling the key points (or mirroring the file’s **§ Tell the next chat**). Do not end the turn with only a note that the file was updated; the user should have the actual words to start the next thread with.
4. On any handoff to the next chat, **include the session’s *last note*** in **`PASSDOWN-NEXT-CHAT.md`**: the user’s final ask, open question, or **pending list** (see that file’s **§ For the assistant** item 4 and **Open / follow-ups**). **Do not** end a passdown update with only a version bump.
5. **Supabase Edge** (`supabase/functions/*/index.ts`): when changing a function, **bump `EDGE_FUNCTION_VERSION`** in the same change, then **redeploy**; JSON includes **`edge: { name, version }`** for live verification. Ship **`package.json` / `CHANGELOG.md`** with that commit per repo release habit.

Partner rule: **`.cursor/rules/compute-neighbors-cron.mdc`** (cron scaling detail).
